---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import WhatsAppFloat from '../../components/WhatsAppFloat.astro';
import InteractiveMap from '../../components/InteractiveMap.astro';
import { whatsappLinks } from '../../data/site';
import { resolveImage } from '../../utils/images';

const locale = 'en';
const arqueologiaImg = resolveImage('/images/Arqueologia.jpg');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us"
  description="Learn the story of Mallku, our mission to share the archaeology of the NOA, and the team of specialized guides that makes each experience possible."
  locale={locale}
>
  <WhatsAppFloat />
  <Header locale={locale} />

  <main>
    <!-- HERO NOSOTROS -->
    <section class="hero-nosotros">
      <div class="wrap text-center">
        <h1>About <span class="accent">Mallku</span></h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">
          Archaeological tourism with soul. We connect curious travelers with the deep history of Northwestern Argentina.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SIGNIFICADO -->
    <section class="section section-light">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="content-grid">
          <div class="content-text">
            <h2>What does Mallku mean?</h2>
            <p>
              <strong>Mallku</strong> (also spelled Mallqu or Mallco) is an Aymara and Quechua word that literally means <em>"condor"</em>, but it doesn't refer only to the bird.
            </p>
            <p>
              In Andean cultures, the Mallku is a <strong>sacred figure</strong>: a guardian of the mountains, a symbol of wisdom, height, spiritual leadership, and connection with the ancestors.
            </p>
            <p>
              The Mallku is not just the one who flies over the Andes, but the one who <strong>observes from above, protects the territory, and keeps alive the memory</strong> of the peoples.
            </p>
            <p>
              That is our spirit: to be guardians of the archaeological memory of the NOA, sharing its richness with those who wish to discover it.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="content-image">
            <div class="logo-showcase">
              <img src="/images/logos/alta-calidad.png" alt="Mallku - The Andean Condor" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HISTORIA -->
    <section class="section section-dark">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="content-grid reverse">
          <div class="content-text">
            <h2>Our History</h2>
            <p>
              Mallku was born with the goal of <strong>spreading the archaeology of Tucum&aacute;n</strong> through tourism, as a proposal that combines exploration, ancestral culture, and connection with the territory.
            </p>
            <p>
              We are an archaeological excursion company based in Tucum&aacute;n, Argentina, that invites curious travelers to discover the cultural richness of past and present: <strong>ancient cities, Andean culture, trails, pathways, and mysteries in ancestral landscapes</strong>.
            </p>
            <p>
              Spaces that hold memories and historical secrets...
            </p>
            <p class="highlight-text">
              "Travel with us to the past, live your present. Tucum&aacute;n as you've never seen it."
            </p>
            <p>
              Our identity fuses the modern with the ancestral: a current, contemporary proposal that breathes history.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="content-image">
            <Image src={arqueologiaImg} alt="Archaeology in Tucum&aacute;n" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- NUESTRO GUIA -->
    <section class="section section-light">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="content-grid">
          <div class="guide-photo">
            <div class="photo-placeholder">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <path d="M12 12c2.21 0 4-1.79 4-4s-1.79-4-4-4-4 1.79-4 4 1.79 4 4 4zm0 2c-2.67 0-8 1.34-8 4v2h16v-2c0-2.66-5.33-4-8-4z"/>
              </svg>
              <p>Guide photo</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="guide-info">
            <h2>Our Guides</h2>
            <p class="guide-title">Archaeologists &middot; Professional tourism guides</p>
            <p>
              Every Mallku excursion is led by a professional with training in archaeology and the history of Northwestern Argentina. This is not a conventional tour guide: it's someone who has studied these sites, walked these hills hundreds of times, and knows every wall, every terrace, and every story behind the stones.
            </p>
            <p>
              Their passion for outreach turns each outing into an experience where the landscape gains meaning. It's not enough to see Quilmes or the Menhirs &mdash; you need someone to explain why they matter, what happened there, and what they mean today.
            </p>
            <p>
              That level of depth is what sets Mallku apart from any other excursion in the region.
            </p>
            <p>
              They are Pablo and Mauro, archaeologists graduated from the prestigious Universidad Nacional de Tucum√°n, with academic experience and fieldwork throughout Northwestern Argentina. Their profile combines scientific rigor and a guiding vocation: they lead archaeological tourism experiences with expert landscape reading, heritage interpretation, and a respectful approach to communities and territory. Pablo specializes in rural community tourism, while Mauro focuses on rock art studies, bringing a precise perspective for understanding pre-Hispanic sites, records, and cultural contexts.
            </p>
            <div class="guide-stats">
              <div class="guide-stat">
                <span class="stat-number">+500</span>
                <span class="stat-label">travelers accompanied</span>
              </div>
              <div class="guide-stat">
                <span class="stat-number">6</span>
                <span class="stat-label">archaeological sites</span>
              </div>
              <div class="guide-stat">
                <span class="stat-number">100%</span>
                <span class="stat-label">small groups</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="section-divider"><span>&#9670;</span></div>

    <!-- MISION Y VISION -->
    <section class="section section-terracota">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="mission-grid">
          <div class="mission-card">
            <h3>Mission</h3>
            <p>
              To offer authentic, educational, and transformative archaeological experiences that connect people with the cultural heritage of northern Argentina.
            </p>
            <p>
              We design excursions to historical sites and sacred landscapes, guided by passionate professionals, to <strong>value the past, care for the present, and project a tourism with purpose</strong>.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="mission-card">
            <h3>Vision</h3>
            <p>
              To be the leading brand in archaeological tourism in Tucum&aacute;n, promoting a model of conscious, cultural exploration that respects ancestral roots and the natural environment.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>To inspire travelers from around the world to reconnect with the living history</strong> that inhabits the soil of Tucum&aacute;n.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- VALORES -->
    <section class="section section-light">
      <div class="wrap text-center">
        <h2 class="section-title">Our Values</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">The principles that guide every excursion we design</p>

        <div class="values-grid">
          <div class="value-card">
            <div class="value-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M16 11c1.66 0 2.99-1.34 2.99-3S17.66 5 16 5s-3 1.34-3 3 1.34 3 3 3zm-8 0c1.66 0 2.99-1.34 2.99-3S9.66 5 8 5 5 6.34 5 8s1.34 3 3 3zm0 2c-2.33 0-7 1.17-7 3.5V19h14v-2.5c0-2.33-4.67-3.5-7-3.5zm8 0c-.29 0-.62.02-.97.05 1.16.84 1.97 1.97 1.97 3.45V19h6v-2.5c0-2.33-4.67-3.5-7-3.5z"/></svg></div>
            <h4>Respect for indigenous cultures</h4>
            <p>We value the legacy of ancestral peoples, their knowledge and worldviews, sharing their history with responsibility, sensitivity, and rigor.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="value-card">
            <div class="value-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M14 6l-3.75 5 2.85 3.8-1.6 1.2C9.81 13.75 7 10 7 10l-6 8h22L14 6z"/></svg></div>
            <h4>Connection with the territory</h4>
            <p>We promote a deep relationship with the landscapes, hills, and sacred sites, understanding that the land holds living memories.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="value-card">
            <div class="value-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M12 22c4.97 0 9-4.03 9-9-4.97 0-9 4.03-9 9zM5.6 10.25c0 1.38 1.12 2.5 2.5 2.5.53 0 1.01-.16 1.42-.44l-.02.19c0 1.38 1.12 2.5 2.5 2.5s2.5-1.12 2.5-2.5l-.02-.19c.4.28.89.44 1.42.44 1.38 0 2.5-1.12 2.5-2.5 0-1-.59-1.85-1.43-2.25.84-.4 1.43-1.25 1.43-2.25 0-1.38-1.12-2.5-2.5-2.5-.53 0-1.01.16-1.42.44l.02-.19C14.5 2.12 13.38 1 12 1S9.5 2.12 9.5 3.5l.02.19c-.4-.28-.89-.44-1.42-.44-1.38 0-2.5 1.12-2.5 2.5 0 1 .59 1.85 1.43 2.25-.84.4-1.43 1.25-1.43 2.25zM12 5.5c1.38 0 2.5 1.12 2.5 2.5s-1.12 2.5-2.5 2.5S9.5 9.38 9.5 8s1.12-2.5 2.5-2.5zM3 13c0 4.97 4.03 9 9 9-4.97 0-9-4.03-9-9z"/></svg></div>
            <h4>Conscious tourism</h4>
            <p>We offer experiences that invite reflection, learning, and reconnection with what's essential. We believe in tourism that doesn't consume but engages.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="value-card">
            <div class="value-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M21 5c-1.11-.35-2.33-.5-3.5-.5-1.95 0-4.05.4-5.5 1.5-1.45-1.1-3.55-1.5-5.5-1.5S2.45 4.9 1 6v14.65c0 .25.25.5.5.5.1 0 .15-.05.25-.05C3.1 20.45 5.05 20 6.5 20c1.95 0 4.05.4 5.5 1.5 1.35-.85 3.8-1.5 5.5-1.5 1.65 0 3.35.3 4.75 1.05.1.05.15.05.25.05.25 0 .5-.25.5-.5V6c-.6-.45-1.25-.75-2-1zm0 13.5c-1.1-.35-2.3-.5-3.5-.5-1.7 0-4.15.65-5.5 1.5V8c1.35-.85 3.8-1.5 5.5-1.5 1.2 0 2.4.15 3.5.5v11.5z"/></svg></div>
            <h4>Accessible outreach</h4>
            <p>We are committed to sharing history, making archaeology accessible to everyone. We translate knowledge into clear, engaging language.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="value-card">
            <div class="value-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M12 1L3 5v6c0 5.55 3.84 10.74 9 12 5.16-1.26 9-6.45 9-12V5l-9-4zm0 10.99h7c-.53 4.12-3.28 7.79-7 8.94V12H5V6.3l7-3.11v8.8z"/></svg></div>
            <h4>Heritage preservation</h4>
            <p>We work with ethics, preserving archaeological sites and the natural balance of the spaces we visit.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="value-card">
            <div class="value-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M12 10.9c-.61 0-1.1.49-1.1 1.1s.49 1.1 1.1 1.1c.61 0 1.1-.49 1.1-1.1s-.49-1.1-1.1-1.1zM12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm2.19 12.19L6 18l3.81-8.19L18 6l-3.81 8.19z"/></svg></div>
            <h4>Explorer spirit</h4>
            <p>We foster curiosity and learning as a driving force, the desire to explore history in the present.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- MAPA -->
    <section class="section section-dark">
      <div class="wrap">
        <h2 class="section-title text-center">Our destinations</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle text-center">The archaeological sites we visit on our excursions</p>
        <div style="margin-top: var(--space-xl);">
          <InteractiveMap />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section section-light">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="cta-box-light">
          <h2>Want to explore the NOA with us?</h2>
          <p>Write to us and we'll tell you everything about our upcoming departures.</p>
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href={whatsappLinks.fechas} target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Inquire via WhatsApp
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer locale={locale} />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero-nosotros {
    padding: 80px 0 60px;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 50% at 50% 0%, rgba(209, 107, 56, 0.15), transparent),
      var(--color-bg-dark);
  }

  .hero-nosotros h1 {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 56px);
  }

  .hero-nosotros .accent {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .hero-lead {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: rgba(239, 227, 214, 0.8);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Content Grid */
  .content-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-2xl);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .content-grid.reverse {
    direction: rtl;
  }

  .content-grid.reverse > * {
    direction: ltr;
  }

  .content-text h2 {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
    font-size: 32px;
  }

  .section-light .content-text h2 {
    color: var(--azul);
  }

  .content-text p {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .section-light .content-text p {
    color: var(--marron);
  }

  .highlight-text {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--color-primary) !important;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-primary);
    margin: var(--space-md) 0 !important;
  }

  .logo-showcase {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: var(--space-2xl) var(--space-xl);
    background: transparent;
  }

  .logo-showcase img {
    max-width: 320px;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .section-dark .content-image > img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    min-height: 500px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .image-placeholder {
    aspect-ratio: 4/3;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(209, 107, 56, 0.2), rgba(6, 27, 56, 0.1));
    border: 2px dashed var(--color-primary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .image-placeholder.dark {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(239, 227, 214, 0.1), rgba(209, 107, 56, 0.1));
    border-color: var(--color-line-light);
  }

  .image-placeholder span {
    font-size: 64px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .image-placeholder p {
    font-size: 14px;
    opacity: 0.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .section-light .image-placeholder p {
    color: var(--marron);
  }

  /* Guide Section */
  .guide-photo {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .photo-placeholder {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 360px;
    aspect-ratio: 3/4;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(209, 107, 56, 0.08), rgba(6, 27, 56, 0.05));
    border: 2px dashed var(--color-line-dark);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .photo-placeholder svg {
    width: 64px;
    height: 64px;
    fill: var(--terracota);
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .photo-placeholder p {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--marron);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .guide-info h2 {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-xs);
    font-size: 32px;
    color: var(--azul);
  }

  .guide-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 14px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--terracota) !important;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md) !important;
  }

  .guide-info p {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--marron);
  }

  .guide-stats {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    padding-top: var(--space-lg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-line-dark);
  }

  .guide-stat {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--terracota);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--marron);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  /* Mission Grid */
  .mission-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .mission-card {
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
  }

  .mission-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
    font-size: 28px;
  }

  .mission-card p {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .mission-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Values Grid */
  .values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .value-card {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-line-dark);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    text-align: left;
  }

  .value-icon {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--terracota);
  }

  .value-icon svg {
    width: 28px;
    height: 28px;
    fill: currentColor;
  }

  .value-card h4 {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-xs);
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--azul);
  }

  .value-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--marron);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* CTA Light */
  .cta-box-light {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-2xl);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-primary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    background: #fff;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-box-light h2 {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
    font-size: 32px;
    color: var(--azul);
  }

  .cta-box-light p {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg);
    color: var(--marron);
  }

  @media (max-width: 980px) {
    .content-grid,
    .content-grid.reverse {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      direction: ltr;
    }

    .content-image {
      order: -1;
    }

    .logo-showcase {
      padding: var(--space-md);
    }

    .logo-showcase img {
      max-width: 180px;
    }

    .mission-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .values-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .guide-stats {
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: var(--space-md);
    }

    .photo-placeholder {
      max-width: 260px;
    }
  }
</style>
